{"id": 225048246, "title": "Cleveland Clinic names new chair of genomic medicine", "text": "CLEVELAND, Ohio\u2014The Cleveland Clinic has tapped a new name to head up its department of genomic medicine. Dr. Russell P. Bowler will take over the role previously held by Dr. Charis Eng, who founded the Department of Genomic Medicine in 2005. Eng will continue to serve as director of Genomic Research Strategies in the Chief Research & Academic Office. In his new position as chair of the renamed Department of Systems Biology & Genome Sciences, Bowler will lead a team of more than 80 genomic scientists and develop the research strategy for Cleveland Clinic\u2019s growing genomic and systems biology research programs. Bowler joins Cleveland Clinic from National Jewish Health in Colorado where he was director of the Precision Medicine Program. He is a practicing physician-scientist and a professor of medicine at the University of Colorado, with over 24 years of experience in studying how biological and environmental factors influence individual risk of developing lung diseases. \u201cDr. Bowler is one of the highest-cited proteomics experts in the world and has published over 300 manuscripts,\u201d wrote the Clinic in a statement announcing Bowler\u2019s appointment. \u201cHis research is supported by federally funded grants and industry contracts and has led to multiple patents. He is a leader of genetics, proteomics and multi-omics in the NIH TransOmic Precision Medicine Program.\u201d He has degrees from Stanford, the University of California at San Francisco, and Colorado.", "summary": "The Cleveland Clinic has tapped a new name to head up its department of genomic medicine", "url": "https://www.cleveland.com/news/2024/05/cleveland-clinic-names-new-chair-of-genomic-medicine.html", "image": "https://www.cleveland.com/resizer/v2/QM2645UVEJBUHJBF3YP7PDYQLY.jpg?auth=3064683da61fb8c4d027953a26ed074e94c4b911e17c0c815797fcc9baf58916&width=1280&quality=90", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 14:07:45", "author": "Gretchen Cuda Kroen,Gretchen Cuda Kroen, Cleveland.com", "authors": ["Gretchen Cuda Kroen", "Gretchen Cuda Kroen, Cleveland.com"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.14}